Denver Dolls present "The Naughty List"","startTime":null,"eventDescription":"Join The Denver Dolls for a fun, theatrical night of music ranging from country to classical about all the ways to get on "The Naughty List" this Christmas! Including works by Gershwin, Jason Robert Brown, Weill, Bolcom, Debussy, Dolly Parton, The Dresden Dolls, Regina Spektor and more! Featuring special guests Dave Devine (guitar), Daniella Theresia (mezzo-soprano) and Aaron Melon (trumpet).

The Denver Dolls (Adriana Teodoro-Dier and Corinne Denny) worked together for several years on various classical projects before realizing they both shared a love for Cabaret and fun music in general.

Adriana Teodoro-Dier (piano) is a Renaissance woman who just refuses to quit. She has a fancy-schmancy Doctorate in Collaborative Piano Performance but loves to play just about anything from any genre, so long as it doesn't suck. By the way, she paints crazy wild abstract art, has a BA in physics, does her own plumbing repairs, and wrestles grizzlies in her spare time. Well, maybe figurative grizzlies. 
www.AdrianaTD.com

Corinne Denny (soprano) is a crafty, animal-loving singer with her own fancy-schmancy MM in Opera and Musical Theatre Performance. She's currently studying for a Performer's Certificate in Voice at University of Denver because she'd like to stay a student forever. Look for Corinne this spring in DU's production of Die Fledermaus as Rosalinda and in Boulder Opera's The Firebringers (by local composer Chappell Kingsland) as the Rainbow Crow. 
www.corinnedenny.com
